@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Quad_Q' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Quad_Q runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To move a peg (space with a rectangular shape on it), just click
on it with the mouse pointer and then click on the empty space
(space with a small dot) where you want to move the peg. You can
only move a peg 2 spaces horizontally or vertically. If the move is
possible, the selected peg will go there.

  'Quad_Q' features two ways to play:

-The Normal game: You jump over a @{b}peg@{ub} and that peg will be removed.
                  Try to remove all the pegs until only one is left,
                  preferably where the empty space was located at
                  the start.

-The Inverted play: You jump over an @{b}empty space@{ub} and a peg will
                    appear there, just as if you would play the
                    normal game backward. Try to 'fill' up the
                    board until only one empty space is left,
                    preferably where the peg was located at the
                    start.

  When there are no possible moves, the game ends and Quad_Q
displays how many pegs (or empty spaces for the 'Inverted' game)
are remaining.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

-New Game:             Restarts the game.

-About...:             Displays the informations about the game.

-Normal/Inverted:      This is a toggle button between the 'Normal'
                       and the 'Inverted' game.

-4 by 4...7 by 7 Quad: To choose between the 4 game board sizes.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

